
[1]penny

   PEN'NY, n. plu. pennies or pence. Pennies denotes the number of coins;
   pence the amount of pennies in value.

   1. An ancient English silver coin; but now an imaginary money of
   account, twelve of which are equal to a shilling. It is the radical
   denomination from which English coin is numbered.

   2. In ancient English statutes, any or all silver money.

   3. Proverbially, a small sum. He will not lend a penny.

   4. Money in general.

   Be sure to turn the penny.
